cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with identifying polynomial-time solvable classes of constraint satisfaction problems, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the purview of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - Constraint satisfaction problems are a common modeling tool in artificial intelligence, and the paper proposes a new class of polynomial-time solvable instances, which is of interest to the AI community. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper deals with the complexity of constraint satisfaction problems and identifies a new class of instances that can be solved in polynomial time, which is of interest to the computational complexity community. 
4. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - Constraint satisfaction problems are closely related to logic, and the paper proposes a new structural property, fractional edge cover number, which can make the problem tractable. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The paper introduces the notion of fractional hypertree width, which is a structural property that can be used to solve constraint satisfaction problems. This is of interest to the computational geometry community, which deals with similar structural properties in geometric algorithms.
